== Pickled Onion ==

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced).

Put the @rice vinegar{1} into a #small bowl{} and add the @sugar{1} for the pickle.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, add half the red onion and stir to coat. Set aside.

== Vegetables and Garlic ==

Halve the @bell pepper{2} and discard the cores and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Beef ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

When the oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and cook until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir the peppers and remaining red onion into the mince and continue cooking until
softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

== Sriracha Mayo ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C.

Meanwhile, mix half the @sriracha sauce{1} with the @mayonnaise{4} in a small bowl.
> Add less sriracha if you don't like heat.

== Assembly ==

When the onions and peppers are softened and the beef is cooked through, add the
garlic and @ginger puree{½} to the pan. IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer
pink in the middle.

Stir and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @soy sauce{25}, @ketjap manis{1}, @sugar{1} for the sauce and remaining sriracha.
Bring to a bubble and remove from the heat.

Meanwhile, pop the @plain taco tortilla{6} onto a #baking tray{} and into your oven to
warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Lay out the tortillas on plates (3 per person).

Spread on the sriracha mayo with the back of a spoon.

Top with spoonfuls of the beef mixture and finish with the pickled red onion -
as much as you'd like.

> Tacos are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in! Enjoy!